ğŸŒ What is DOM?

**DOM (Document Object Model)** is the **tree structure of HTML elements** in the browser.

ğŸ“Œ Browser updates DOM when:

* Content changes
* Styles change
* User interacts

âŒ Direct DOM manipulation is **slow**

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

âŒ Problem with Real DOM

* Every change updates the whole DOM
* Repainting & reflow are expensive
* Poor performance for large apps

ğŸ“Œ Example:

```js
document.getElementById("count").innerHTML = count;
```

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸŒ³ What is Virtual DOM?

**Virtual DOM** is a **lightweight JavaScript copy of the Real DOM** maintained by React.

ğŸ“Œ It is:

* Fast
* In-memory
* JS object representation of UI

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ”„ How Virtual DOM Works

1. React creates a **Virtual DOM**
2. UI changes â†’ new Virtual DOM created
3. React compares old & new Virtual DOM
4. Only changed parts are updated in Real DOM

âœ” Faster updates
âœ” Better performance

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ§  Virtual DOM vs Real DOM

| Virtual DOM     | Real DOM           |
| --------------- | ------------------ |
| JS object       | Actual browser DOM |
| Fast            | Slow               |
| Minimal updates | Full re-render     |
| Used by React   | Used by browser    |

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ” What is Reconciliation?

**Reconciliation** is the process where React:

* Compares old Virtual DOM with new Virtual DOM
* Finds differences
* Updates only changed nodes in Real DOM

ğŸ“Œ This comparison process is called **Diffing Algorithm**

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ§© Diffing Algorithm (Simple Explanation)

React follows smart rules:

1. Elements with **same type** â†’ update attributes
2. Elements with **different type** â†’ destroy & recreate
3. Uses **keys** to track list items

ğŸ“Œ Makes reconciliation very fast

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ”‘ Importance of `key` in Lists (Very Important â­)

```jsx
{items.map(item => (
  <li key={item.id}>{item.name}</li>
))}
```

ğŸ“Œ Keys help React:

* Identify elements uniquely
* Avoid unnecessary re-renders
* Improve performance

âŒ Bad practice:

```jsx
key={index}
```

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ”„ Re-rendering in React

React re-renders when:

* State changes
* Props change
* Parent component re-renders

ğŸ“Œ Re-render â‰  DOM update
ğŸ“Œ React updates DOM **only if needed**

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ§  State Change Flow

```text
State Change
   â†“
New Virtual DOM
   â†“
Diffing
   â†“
Minimal Real DOM Update
```

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

âš¡ Why React is Fast?

* Virtual DOM
* Efficient diffing
* Batch updates
* Minimal DOM manipulation

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ§ª Example: State Update

```jsx
